regardless of race and location, have a built sign language of sorts. For example, the large majority of cultures will recognize gestures such as pointing, head shaking, shrugging, etc.. A combination of these gestures, along with similar but more personalized and individual ones, can form an effective means of communication for a deaf child that is not taught a sign language. %0a%3c %0a%3c Sources:%0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Home_sign%0a%3c https://www.taylorfrancis.com/chapters/mono/10.4324/9780429020872-7/homesign-systems-joseph-hill-diane-lillo-martin-sandra-wood%0a%3c https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/15248372.2013.803970%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
